<p>c)</p>

<p>Based on the theorem above, prove that 
\(\nabla{x}(x^{T}Ax) = 2Ax\)
for any column vector $x \in \mathbb{R}^{n}$ and any symmetric $n \times n$ matrix $A$</p>

<p>d)</p>

<p>Based on the theorems above, prove that
\(\nabla_{x}[(Ax + b)^{T}(Ax + b)] = 2A^{T}(Ax + b)\)
for any column vector $x \in \mathbb{R}^{n}$, any symmetric $n \times n$ matrix $A$, and any constant column vector $b \in \mathbb{R}^{n}$</p>
